Core Job Responsibilities:

Developing and Supporting Quantitative models for HTI's cash equities agency trading platform.

Details:

Haitong International has a suite of existing quantitative models which feed into the algorithmic trading engine including volume forecasts, fair value estimation and volatility forecasts;
We are looking for a mid-level quantitative analyst with R/Python skills who is capable of maintaining and further developing these models;
They will also be responsible for developing new models in time;
This person will be the key contact for model related questions and may be required to explain functionality to clients;
Future responsibilities include working on proprietary trading strategies.

Programming Skills (In order of importance):

Java, R, Python, q/KDB.

Requirements :

Excellent academic record of bachelor's degree (or above) from a top university, major in Computer Science, engineering or other quantitative related discipline;
A PhD/Masters that focuses on Machine Learning/Data Science/Computer Science/Physics/Mathematics/Statistics is an advantage;
Dynamic Linear Models experience;
Familiarity with Neural Nets and other ML techniques;
Independent research experience;
Highly motivated and competitive;
Learning curiosity & agility;
A good communicator and team player.




We are committed to build a team of competence individuals who have acquired relevant local solid working experience and with diversified exposure to work together with us. Applicants who do not hear from us within 6 weeks may consider their applications unsuccessful.

